This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Natural Language Processing techniques for biomedical information extraction. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields are closely related to NLP. Additionally, it may belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper discusses techniques for extracting information from biomedical texts. Finally, it may belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the field of biomedical information extraction has important implications for healthcare and society.
